EAccording%20to%20a%20March%20Goldman%20Sachs%20report%2C%20funding%20of%20creator%20economy%20companies%20peaked%20in%202021%2C%20slowed%20between%202022%20and%202023%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Breaccelerated%26quot%3B%20in%202024.%20An%20estimated%20%241.5%20billion%20was%20invested%20in%20creator%20economy%20startups%20in%202024%2C%20per%20Goldman%20Sachs'%20analysis%20of%20PitchBook%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%20projects%20the%20creator%20economy%20will%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcreator-economy-250-billion-market-and-here-to-stay-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%24480%20billion%20industry%20by%202027%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20creator%20economy%20has%20matured%20into%20a%20marketing%20layer%20that%20spans%20across%20industries%2C%20said%20Maya%20Bakhai%2C%20founder%20and%20general%20partner%20of%20Spice%20Capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20single%20company%20needs%20to%20have%20an%20attention%20strategy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%20in%202025%2C%20there's%20already%20been%20a%20handful%20of%20flashy%20fundraising%20rounds%20from%20creator%20startups.%20Investors%20are%20betting%20on%20startups%20that%20leverage%20creators%20to%20boost%20other%20industries%20like%20e-commerce%20or%20publishing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarting%20the%20year%20off%2C%20Whatnot%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhatnot-ceo-fundraising-round-expansion-plans-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elive%20shopping%20app%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20raised%20a%20%24265%20million%20Series%20E%20funding%20round%20at%20a%20valuation%20of%20%244.9%20billion.%20Later%20in%20January%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-shopping-startups-funding-tiktok-ban-whatnot-shopmy-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EShopMy%2C%20a%20social%20shopping%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20affiliate%20marketing%20company%2C%20announced%20a%20%2477.5%20million%20Series%20B.%20And%20last%20month%2C%20Substack%2C%20a%20newsletter%20platform%20that's%20fueled%20a%20wave%20of%20creators%2C%20announced%20its%20%24100%20million%20Series%20C.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20hot%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20are%20particularly%20interested%20in%20AI-powered%20creative%20tools%20because%20they%20are%20positioned%20to%20help%20creators%20with%20what%20they%20do%20best%3A%20make%20content.%20Menlo%20Ventures%20invested%20in%20Flora%2C%20an%20AI%20tool%20for%20digital%20creatives%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESasha%20Kaletsky%2C%20managing%20partner%20at%20Creator%20Ventures%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20firm%20is%20excited%20by%20startups%20that%20%26quot%3Bempower%20the%20long%20tail%20of%20creators%20to%20be%20able%20to%20create%20the%20content%20that%20their%20audience%20loves%20faster%2C%20cheaper%2C%20better.%26quot%3B%20The%20firm%20recently%20backed%20tools%20like%20Creatify%2C%20which%20generates%20ads%20using%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20investors%20also%20see%20the%20creator%20economy%20as%20fitting%20into%20their%20focus%20on%20business-to-business%20(B2B)%20technology%2C%20or%20view%20creators%20as%20an%20intersection%20between%20consumers%20and%20businesses%2C%20which%20has%20fanned%20the%20flame%20for%20another%20VC%20buzzword%3A%20prosumer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaley%20Bryant%2C%20a%20principal%20at%20Hustle%20Fund%2C%20said%20she%20categorizes%20creators%20as%20small%20to%20medium%20businesses.%20The%20firm%20recently%20invested%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-meta-employees-launch-startup-comedians-punchup-live-pitch-deck-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPunchup%20Live%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20ticketing%20marketplace%20for%20comedy%20creators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20is%20highlighting%2016%20VC%20firms%20and%20their%20partners%20who%20are%20backing%20creator%20economy%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20and%20creators%20themselves.%20This%20list%2C%20%3Ca%20hre