%20are%20now%20subject%20to%20full-time%20in-office%20work%20mandates%2C%20the%20report%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Placer.ai%20Nationwide%20Office%20Building%20Index%20analyzes%20foot%20traffic%20data%20from%20about%201%2C000%20commercial%20office%20buildings%20across%20the%20country.%20The%20latest%20report%20found%20that%20office%20visits%20in%20July%20of%20this%20year%20were%20up%2010.7%25%20compared%20to%20July%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOffice%20visits%20in%20July%202025%20were%20down%2021.8%25%20compared%20to%20July%202019%2C%20shortly%20before%20the%20coronavirus%20pandemic%20forced%20office%20shutdowns%20around%20the%20world%20the%20following%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20cities%2C%20however%2C%20are%20bouncing%20back.%20Employees%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20driven%20largely%20by%20workers%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-rto-banks-hedge-funds-private-equity-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efinancial%20sector%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20are%20subject%20to%20strict%20RTO%20requirements%2C%20saw%201.3%25%20office%20foot%20traffic%20growth%20in%20July%202025%20compared%20to%202019%20%E2%80%94%20a%20first%20since%20Placer.ai%20began%20tracking%20these%20trends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlacer.ai%20found%20Miami%20came%20close%20behind%2C%20posting%20just%20a%200.1%25%20lag%20compared%20to%20its%202019%20foot%20traffic.%20Atlanta%20and%20Dallas%20also%20saw%20more%20in-office%20foot%20traffic%20than%20the%20national%20average%20compared%20to%202019%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESan%20Francisco%20saw%20the%20greatest%20gains%20year-over-year%2C%20with%2021.6%25%20visit%20growth%20compared%20to%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20if%20you%20haven't%20been%20called%20back%20to%20the%20office%20yet%2C%20you're%20increasingly%20in%20the%20minority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMajor%20employers%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-requiring-return-to-office-rto-mandate%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAm