Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20conscious%20of%20our%20need%20to%20have%20credibility%20even%20though%20we%20may%20not%20have%20up-to-date%20combat%20experience%20of%20this%20type%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20I%20don't%20see%20that%20as%20a%20disqualifying%20factor%2C%20if%20you%20like%2C%20because%20I%20think%20we%20do%20have%20the%20institutional%20credibility%20and%20expertise%20that%20what%20we're%20teaching%20is%20genuinely%20valued%2C%20not%20only%20at%20the%20top%20end%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20military%2C%20but%20right%20all%20the%20way%20down%20through%20to%20those%20who%20actually%20go%20through%20the%20training.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a6bd3be-41f9-4153-8359-e01eaeeac266%5C%22%3EA%20different%20type%20of%20war%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20West%20hasn't%20fought%20a%20major%20war%20against%20a%20powerful%2C%20industrialized%20military%20in%20decades.%20Most%20NATO%20combat%20experience%20in%20recent%20memory%20comes%20from%20the%20counterinsurgency%20and%20counterterrorism%20campaigns%20in%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan%2C%20where%20Western%20forces%20enjoyed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnato-must-learn-from-ukraine-keep-air-supremacy-us-general-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eair%20superiority%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20faced%20smaller%2C%20less-equipped%20adversaries.%20Some%20Interflex%20trainers%20weren't%20even%20in%20Iraq%20or%20Afghanistan%2C%20having%20joined%20after%20those%20conflicts%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-did-russia-invade-ukraine-putin-politics-motive-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EUkraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20battling%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20militaries%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-russia-death-by-thousand-cuts-tactic-stress-ukraines-forces-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egrinding%2C%20high-casualty%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20no%20control%20of%20the%20skies.%20Russia's%20relentless%20artillery%20fire%2C%20missile%20strikes%2C%20and%20widespread%20use%20of%20drones%20have%20reshaped%20the%20battlefield%20in%20ways%20NATO%20has%20not%20faced%20for%20generations%2C%20or%20in%20some%20cases%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20soldiers%20fire%20toward%20Russian%20position%20on%20the%20frontline%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%20region%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20Saturday%2C%20June%2024%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6499634165b9ce0018a4b93d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20soldiers%20fire%20toward%20Russian%20position%20on%20the%20frontline%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%20region%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20on%20June%2024%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FEfrem%20Lukatsky%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20Western%20militaries%20were%20heavily%20focused%20on%20counterinsurgency%20skills%20while%20maintaining%20a%20theoretical%20capability%20for%20large-scale%20war.%20Boardman%20acknowledged%20this%2C%20while%20saying%20the%20UK%20did%20not%20lose%20the%20capability%20for%20major%20operations%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20naturally%20you%20do%20shape%20yourself%20for%20the%20moment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20Boardman%20said%2C%20there's%20a%20renewed%20focus%20on%20combating%20a%20well-armed%20foe.%20That%20has%20meant%20dusting%20off%20tactics%20such%20as%20trench%20warfare%20and%20learning%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20from%20Ukraine's%20front-line%20soldiers%20about%20emerging%20threats%20like%20exploding%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f0e12d4d-d51a-4f61-bba7-39ca2532fd4d%5C%22%3EA%20win-win%20scenario%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoardman%20said%20Ukrainian%20soldiers%20bring%20%E2%80%9Ca%20lot%20of%20valuable%20military%20experience%E2%80%9D%20to%20the%20training.%20That%20experience%20often%20challenges%20NATO%E2%80%99s%20best%20practices%20and%20leads%20to%20adjustments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Western%20officials%20and%20instructors%20behind%20Interflex%20are%20%26quot%3Bapproaching%20it%20with%20a%20humility%20of%20approach%20that%20allows%20us%20to%20provide%20our%20opinions%20and%20our%20ideas%20and%20our%20teaching%2C%20but%20also%20learn%20from%20some%20of%20the%20feedback%20that%20we%20get%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20when%20learning%20casualty%20evacuation%2C%20Ukrainians%20sometimes%20reject%20NATO's%20extraction%20techniques%2C%20explaining%20that%20in%20their%20war%2C%20it%20may%20be%20safer%20to%20wait%20until%20nightfall%20to%20move%20the%20wounded.%20In%20trench%20warfare%20lessons%2C%20Ukrainians%20sometimes%20correct%20their%20instructors%20based%20on%20tactics%20they%20used%20in%20combat%20just%20weeks%20earlier.%20Those%20insights%20are%20then%20incorporated%20into%20the%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20medic%20in%20Bakhmut%20trench%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6407b44012573900187953e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20medic%20runs%20through%20a%20partially%20dug%20trench%20on%20the%20frontline%20outside%20Bakhmut%20on%20March%205%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Moore%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20sides%20are%20learning%20from%20the%20training%20exercise.%20Key%20lessons%20from%20Ukraine%20are%20feeding%20directly%20into%20Western%20planning%20as%20militaries%20across%20Europe%20prepare%20for%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20future%20conflict%20with%20Russia.%20And%20NATO%20allies%20are%20sharing%20their%20skills%20with%20Ukraine.%20Finland%2C%20for%20example%2C%20brings%20forest-warfare%20expertise%20to%20Interflex%20that%20Ukraine%20lacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20question%20that's%20a%20benefit%20to%20the%20Ukrainians%2C%26quot%3B%20Boardman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20explained%20that%20there%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Breally%20rich%20mutual%20understanding%20going%20on%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20the%20training%20program%20%26quot%3Bends%20up%20with%20the%20sum%20being%20much%20greater%20than%20the%20parts%2C%20which%20is%20really%20valuable%20for%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%E2%80%99s%20expertise%20with%20drones%2C%20particularly%20the%20first-person-view%20attack%20drones%2C%20has%20been%20especially%20valuable%2C%20especially%20considering%20the%20changes%20to%20the%20operating%20environment%20since%20Iraq%20and%20Afghanistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoardman%20said%20that%20while%20the%20UK%20has%20drone%20operators%20and%20instructors%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwe%20are%20not%20currently%20at%20war%2C%20so%20we%20are%20not%20developing%20them%20at%20the%20same%20pace%20that%20the%20Ukrainians%20are.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20Ukraine%20is%20%26quot%3Bvery%20good%20at%20sharing%20the%20understanding%20with%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20also%20helps%20the%20UK%20and%20other%20Western%20militaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225e9865b3-2af7-44c0-ab3b-0302ea4ec44f%5C%22%3EBracing%20for%20more%20war%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBoardman%20said%20he%20recognizes%20that%20it%20can%20be%20a%20bit%20%26quot%3Buncomfortable%26quot%3B%20for%20trainers%20to%20teach%20trench%20assaults%20without%20having%20actually%20done%20it%20personally%2C%20but%20the%20West%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20institutional%20credibility%20from%20past%20military%20operations%20and%20combat%20successes%20that%20give%20%26quot%3Bus%20license%2C%20effectively%2C%20to%20do%20this%20training.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20asking%20for%20the%20training.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20just%20asking%20them%20to%20come%20and%20be%20trained%20here%3B%20it's%20Ukrainians%20who%20are%20asking%20us%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20soldiers%20take%20part%20in%20a%20training%20excerci